<form onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); checkAnswer('module3_mcq_q1')" data-correct-answer="A">
  <strong style="display: block;">Which of the following statements best describes an efficient portfolio?</strong>

  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q1" value="A"> A. A portfolio that maximizes return for a given level of risk</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q1" value="B"> B. A portfolio with the lowest variance regardless of return</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q1" value="C"> C. A portfolio that holds only a single risky asset</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q1" value="D"> D. A portfolio that invests equal amounts in all available assets</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q1" value="E"> E. A portfolio that minimizes beta</label><br>
</form>

<div id="feedback-module3_mcq_q1" class="feedback" data-status="" style="display:none;">
‚úÖ Correct: A. An efficient portfolio is one that offers the highest expected return for a given level of risk.
</div>

:::


  </div>
</div>

<div style="display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;">
  <div style="font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;">Q2.</div>
  <div style="flex: 1;">


::: {.question-block}

<form onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); checkAnswer('module3_mcq_q2')" data-correct-answer="C">
  <strong style="display: block;">The variance of a two‚Äëasset portfolio depends on:</strong>

  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q2" value="A"> A. Only the variances of the individual assets</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q2" value="B"> B. Only the covariance between the assets</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q2" value="C"> C. Both the variances of the individual assets and the covariance between them</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q2" value="D"> D. The average return of the portfolio</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q2" value="E"> E. None of the above</label><br>
</form>

<div id="feedback-module3_mcq_q2" class="feedback" data-status="" style="display:none;">
‚úÖ Correct: C. Portfolio variance combines the individual asset variances and their covariance (or correlation).
</div>

:::


  </div>
</div>

<div style="display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;">
  <div style="font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;">Q3.</div>
  <div style="flex: 1;">

::: {.question-block}

<form onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); checkAnswer('module3_mcq_q3')" data-correct-answer="A">
  <strong style="display: block;">If the correlation between two assets is ‚àí1, combining them in a portfolio:</strong>

  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q3" value="A"> A. Eliminates all risk if the weights are properly chosen</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q3" value="B"> B. Has no effect on the portfolio‚Äôs risk</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q3" value="C"> C. Doubles the portfolio‚Äôs expected return</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q3" value="D"> D. Increases the portfolio‚Äôs variance above either asset‚Äôs variance</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q3" value="E"> E. Makes the assets perfectly positively correlated</label><br>
</form>

<div id="feedback-module3_mcq_q3" class="feedback" data-status="" style="display:none;">
‚úÖ Correct: A. A correlation of ‚àí1 means the assets move perfectly in opposite directions, allowing risk to be eliminated with the right weights.
</div>

:::


  </div>
</div>

<div style="display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;">
  <div style="font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;">Q4.</div>
  <div style="flex: 1;">


::: {.question-block}

<form onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); checkAnswer('module3_mcq_q4')" data-correct-answer="C">
  <strong style="display: block;">Which measure captures only the systematic risk of a stock?</strong>

  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q4" value="A"> A. Standard deviation</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q4" value="B"> B. Variance</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q4" value="C"> C. Beta</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q4" value="D"> D. Arithmetic mean</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q4" value="E"> E. Sharpe ratio</label><br>
</form>

<div id="feedback-module3_mcq_q4" class="feedback" data-status="" style="display:none;">
‚úÖ Correct: C. Beta measures an asset‚Äôs sensitivity to market movements and therefore captures only systematic risk.
</div>

:::


