</div>

<div style="display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;">
  <div style="font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;">Q5.</div>
  <div style="flex: 1;">

::: {.question-block}

<form onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); checkAnswer('module3_mcq_q5')" data-correct-answer="D">
  <strong style="display: block;">In the Capital Asset Pricing Model (CAPM), the expected return of a security is:</strong>

  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q5" value="A"> A. Equal to the risk‚Äëfree rate</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q5" value="B"> B. Inversely proportional to its beta</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q5" value="C"> C. Equal to the average return of the market portfolio</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q5" value="D"> D. A linear function of the security‚Äôs beta and the market risk premium</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q5" value="E"> E. Independent of the security‚Äôs beta</label><br>
</form>

<div id="feedback-module3_mcq_q5" class="feedback" data-status="" style="display:none;">
‚úÖ Correct: D. The CAPM states that E[R] = Rf + Œ≤ √ó (E[Rm] ‚àí Rf), a linear function of beta and the market risk premium.
</div>

:::


  </div>
</div>

<div style="display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 8px;">
  <div style="font-weight: bold; min-width: 40px;">Q6.</div>
  <div style="flex: 1;">


::: {.question-block}

<form onsubmit="event.preventDefault(); checkAnswer('module3_mcq_q6')" data-correct-answer="C">
  <strong style="display: block;">The Sharpe ratio of a portfolio is defined as:</strong>

  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q6" value="A"> A. The portfolio‚Äôs excess return divided by its variance</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q6" value="B"> B. The portfolio‚Äôs beta divided by its return</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q6" value="C"> C. The portfolio‚Äôs excess return divided by its standard deviation</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q6" value="D"> D. The portfolio‚Äôs return divided by its beta</label><br>
  <label><input type="radio" name="module3_mcq_q6" value="E"> E. The portfolio‚Äôs variance divided by the market variance</label><br>
</form>

<div id="feedback-module3_mcq_q6" class="feedback" data-status="" style="display:none;">
‚úÖ Correct: C. The Sharpe ratio measures excess return per unit of total risk (standard deviation).
</div>

:::


  </div>
</div>

